<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[811,1457,567,1134]" box="[813,957,567,593]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[811,1457,567,1134]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">
Shell of medium size (maximum observed length 12.6 mm), thin, translucent, elongate oval to rounded while young to subpentagonal in adult, ventribiconvex. Shell surface smooth with numerous growth lines. Lateral commissures straight, anterior commissure rectimarginate to incipiently sulcate. Hinge line short, slightly curved. Beak suberect to erect. Foramen large, oval, permesothyrid, deltidial plates rudimentary. Ventral valve interior with small teeth supported by divergent dental plates united by a callus closely applied to the valve floor (
<figureCitation box="[945,1088,885,911]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="20.[132,143,1871,1889]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-16@20.[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIG. 12. — Macandrevia emigi n. sp.: A-C, dorsal views of complete specimens (MNHN IB-2013-75-76), South Madagascar, South-West Point Barrow, ATIMO VATAE, stn CP 3589, 132-153 m; D-F, inner view of dorsal valve of young individual (MNHN IB-2013-73), and oblique view (E) and enlargement of posterior part (F) to show details of a loop, paratype, stn CP 3589; G, H, inner view of ventral valve (MNHN IB-2013-74) and tilted view to show dental plates (H), paratype, stn CP 3589; I, dorsal view of complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-72), paratype, Mozambique Channel, Inhambane transect, MAINBAZA, stn CP 3139, 1092- 1195 m; J-Q, complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-71), holotype, Mozambique Channel, Maputo transect, MAINBAZA, stn CC 3170, 949-952 m: J-L, dorsal, anterior and lateral views, M, N, posterior part of ventral valve interior and tilted view to show distinct dental plates,SEM O-Q, interior view of dorsal valve, oblique view, and enlargement of fringe of spines (Q), SEM. Scale bars: A-E, G, M, O, P, 2 mm; F, H, N, 1 mm; I-L, 5 mm; Q, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4578184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4578184/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12H, N</figureCitation>
). Dorsal valve interior with small cardinal process and high inner socket ridges. Inner hinge plates attached directly to the valve floor. Low, short median septum present in early stages of ontogeny (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1363,980,1007]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="20.[132,143,1871,1889]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-16@20.[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIG. 12. — Macandrevia emigi n. sp.: A-C, dorsal views of complete specimens (MNHN IB-2013-75-76), South Madagascar, South-West Point Barrow, ATIMO VATAE, stn CP 3589, 132-153 m; D-F, inner view of dorsal valve of young individual (MNHN IB-2013-73), and oblique view (E) and enlargement of posterior part (F) to show details of a loop, paratype, stn CP 3589; G, H, inner view of ventral valve (MNHN IB-2013-74) and tilted view to show dental plates (H), paratype, stn CP 3589; I, dorsal view of complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-72), paratype, Mozambique Channel, Inhambane transect, MAINBAZA, stn CP 3139, 1092- 1195 m; J-Q, complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-71), holotype, Mozambique Channel, Maputo transect, MAINBAZA, stn CC 3170, 949-952 m: J-L, dorsal, anterior and lateral views, M, N, posterior part of ventral valve interior and tilted view to show distinct dental plates,SEM O-Q, interior view of dorsal valve, oblique view, and enlargement of fringe of spines (Q), SEM. Scale bars: A-E, G, M, O, P, 2 mm; F, H, N, 1 mm; I-L, 5 mm; Q, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4578184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4578184/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
D-F), in adults median septum absent (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1269,1012,1039]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="20.[132,143,1871,1889]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-16@20.[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIG. 12. — Macandrevia emigi n. sp.: A-C, dorsal views of complete specimens (MNHN IB-2013-75-76), South Madagascar, South-West Point Barrow, ATIMO VATAE, stn CP 3589, 132-153 m; D-F, inner view of dorsal valve of young individual (MNHN IB-2013-73), and oblique view (E) and enlargement of posterior part (F) to show details of a loop, paratype, stn CP 3589; G, H, inner view of ventral valve (MNHN IB-2013-74) and tilted view to show dental plates (H), paratype, stn CP 3589; I, dorsal view of complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-72), paratype, Mozambique Channel, Inhambane transect, MAINBAZA, stn CP 3139, 1092- 1195 m; J-Q, complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-71), holotype, Mozambique Channel, Maputo transect, MAINBAZA, stn CC 3170, 949-952 m: J-L, dorsal, anterior and lateral views, M, N, posterior part of ventral valve interior and tilted view to show distinct dental plates,SEM O-Q, interior view of dorsal valve, oblique view, and enlargement of fringe of spines (Q), SEM. Scale bars: A-E, G, M, O, P, 2 mm; F, H, N, 1 mm; I-L, 5 mm; Q, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4578184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4578184/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12O, P</figureCitation>
). Loop long with narrow descending and ascending branches, transverse band moderately broad with short projections, and short spines anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[933,1036,1108,1134]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="20.[132,143,1871,1889]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-16@20.[194,1393,215,1820]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIG. 12. — Macandrevia emigi n. sp.: A-C, dorsal views of complete specimens (MNHN IB-2013-75-76), South Madagascar, South-West Point Barrow, ATIMO VATAE, stn CP 3589, 132-153 m; D-F, inner view of dorsal valve of young individual (MNHN IB-2013-73), and oblique view (E) and enlargement of posterior part (F) to show details of a loop, paratype, stn CP 3589; G, H, inner view of ventral valve (MNHN IB-2013-74) and tilted view to show dental plates (H), paratype, stn CP 3589; I, dorsal view of complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-72), paratype, Mozambique Channel, Inhambane transect, MAINBAZA, stn CP 3139, 1092- 1195 m; J-Q, complete specimen (MNHN IB-2013-71), holotype, Mozambique Channel, Maputo transect, MAINBAZA, stn CC 3170, 949-952 m: J-L, dorsal, anterior and lateral views, M, N, posterior part of ventral valve interior and tilted view to show distinct dental plates,SEM O-Q, interior view of dorsal valve, oblique view, and enlargement of fringe of spines (Q), SEM. Scale bars: A-E, G, M, O, P, 2 mm; F, H, N, 1 mm; I-L, 5 mm; Q, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4578184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4578184/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Fig. 12Q</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
