<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[811,1457,1172,1708]" box="[813,913,1172,1198]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[811,1457,1172,1708]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">
The superfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allan" authorityYear="1940" box="[1001,1139,1204,1230]" class="Rhynchonellata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Zeillerioidea">Zeillerioidea</taxonomicName>
comprises 10 extant species belonging to a single genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Logan 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Logan" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[1142,1453,1236,1262]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Zeilleriidae" genus="Macandrevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1142,1284,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Macandrevia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LOGAN A." box="[1301,1444,1236,1262]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" pagination="3082 - 3115" refId="ref21036" refString="LOGAN A. 2007. - Geographic distribution of extant articulated brachiopods, in SELDEN P. A. (ed.), Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology. Part H. Brachiopoda Revised. Geological Society of America and University of Kansas. Boulder, Colorado and Lawrence, Kansas, vol. 6: 3082 - 3115." type="journal article" year="2007">Logan 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Species of the genus have previously been recorded virtually from pole to pole and usually from cold deep waters (
<bibRefCitation author="COOPER G. A." box="[822,972,1331,1358]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" pagination="911 - 927" refId="ref19434" refString="COOPER G. A. 1975. - Brachiopods from West African waters with examples of collateral evolution. Journal of Paleontology 49: 911 - 927." type="journal article" year="1975">Cooper 1975</bibRefCitation>
) but not from the Indian 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Logan, 2016" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Logan" authorityYear="2016" box="[1263,1334,1331,1357]" genus="Ocean" pageId="17" pageNumber="5" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Ocean</taxonomicName>
or western and central Pacific. This description of a new species, based mainly on 
<specimenCount box="[937,1088,1395,1422]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" type="generic">35 specimens</specimenCount>
from South 
<collectingCountry box="[1236,1368,1395,1421]" name="Madagascar" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, is thus the first record of the genus from the Indian 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Logan, 2016" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Logan" authorityYear="2016" box="[1314,1389,1427,1453]" genus="Ocean" pageId="17" pageNumber="5" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Ocean</taxonomicName>
. Most species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Logan" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[928,1067,1459,1485]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Zeilleriidae" genus="Macandrevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[928,1067,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Macandrevia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are eurybathic, with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jeffreys" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[1309,1414,1460,1485]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Zeilleriidae" genus="Macandrevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="tenera">
<emphasis box="[1309,1414,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">M. tenera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
extending down to 
<quantity box="[1005,1092,1491,1517]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" unit="m" value="4600.0">4600 m</quantity>
but the depth range of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bitner &amp; Logan, 2016" authorityName="Bitner &amp; Logan" authorityYear="2016" box="[1358,1455,1492,1517]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Zeilleriidae" genus="Macandrevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="emigi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1358,1455,1492,1517]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">M. emigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[813,872,1523,1549]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is much less. The new species is comparable in size to the northern Atlantic species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cooper, 1977" authorityName="Cooper" authorityYear="1977" box="[1143,1456,1554,1581]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Zeilleriidae" genus="Macandrevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="novangliae">
<emphasis box="[1143,1295,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">M. novangliae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="COOPER G. A." box="[1303,1456,1555,1581]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 211" refId="ref19462" refString="COOPER G. A. 1977. - Brachiopods from the Caribbean Sea and adjacent waters. Studies in Tropical Oceanography 14: 1 - 211." type="journal article" year="1977">Cooper, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jeffreys, 1876)" baseAuthorityName="Jeffreys" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[859,1129,1586,1613]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Zeilleriidae" genus="Macandrevia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebratulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="tenera">
<emphasis box="[859,959,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">M. tenera</emphasis>
(Jeffreys, 1876)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="COOPER G. A." box="[1142,1290,1586,1613]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" pagination="911 - 927" refId="ref19434" refString="COOPER G. A. 1975. - Brachiopods from West African waters with examples of collateral evolution. Journal of Paleontology 49: 911 - 927." type="journal article" year="1975">Cooper 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="COOPER G. A." box="[1300,1359,1587,1613]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 211" refId="ref19462" refString="COOPER G. A. 1977. - Brachiopods from the Caribbean Sea and adjacent waters. Studies in Tropical Oceanography 14: 1 - 211." type="journal article" year="1977">1977</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="COOPER G. A." box="[1369,1442,1586,1613]" pageId="17" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 35" refId="ref19518" refString="COOPER G. A. 1981 b. - Brachiopoda from the Gulf of Gascogne, France (Recent). Smithsonian Contributions to Paleobiology 44: 1 - 35." type="journal article" year="1981">1981b</bibRefCitation>
), other species are much larger. However, the species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[811,939,1650,1676]" name="Madagascar" pageId="17" pageNumber="22">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
region differs from all hitherto described species in its triangular outline.
</paragraph>
